===Etymology 2===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|swer|lang=enm}}, {{term|swar|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|swær|swǣr|lang=ang}}, {{term|swar|swār|heavy, heavy as a burden, of great weight, oppressive, grievous, painful, unpleasant, sad, feeling or expressing grief, grave, slow, dull, sluggish, slothful, indolent, inactive from weakness, enfeebled, weak|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|swēraz|heavy|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|swēr-|heavy|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|swier||heavy|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|zwaar||heavy, hard, difficult|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|schwer||heavy, hard, difficult|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|svår||heavy, hard, severe|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|serius|sērius|earnest, grave, solemn, serious|lang=la}}.

